{% extends "_base.txt.j2" %}
{% block content -%}
Hi {{ name }},

Your admin credentials (password and TOTP) were just reset via the
recovery runbook at:

  When: {{ when_str }}
  From: {{ ip }}

If you executed this recovery yourself, no action is required.

If you did NOT, the host that runs the application has been compromised.
Treat as an incident:
  1. Rotate every secret in .env (SECRET_KEY, EMAIL_PEPPER, all DB
     and Redis passwords).
  2. Audit every auth_events row since the reset for unfamiliar IPs.
  3. Revoke outstanding sessions in Redis.
{%- endblock %}
